title: For Sale:  Smith and Wesson/Walther P99-40 caliber with extras
postcontent:
Smith and Wesson/Walther P99-40 caliber
 I am selling this amazing gun for $500.00, I will consider offers or trades if reasonable. I will need to see identification.

For an in depth video of this gun see this review on YouTube, (The BEST Self Defense Handgun (SW99; $825 MSRP) — Review & Explanation.)
This Gun is well cared for and finish is excellent with no visible wear or scratches. The gun comes with the following
-Tritium Night Sights
-extra standard sights
-FIVE (5) total Magazines 
- 2 extra floor plates
-lockable padded case
-All factory tools and papers including manual
-extra ballistic nylon carrying case for gun and magazines
-3 changeable back straps to customize grip to owner, small, medium and large

The Smith and Wesson SW-99 is a joint venture pistol between Smith and Wesson and Carl Walther and as the pictures show it is marked with the Walther and Smith and Wesson ID. It is a striker fired semi-automatic pistol with a total capacity of 13+1 in .40 Cal. It has an ambidextrous mag release located on the rear of the trigger guard which itself is oversized to enable ease of use even with gloves on. The SW99 also features a fully supported chamber design, which leaves no portion of the chambered round exposed. Because of this there is less chance of injury to the shooter and/or destruction of the pistol, should the casing head rupture. The unique and ergonomic grip of this pistol was designed by the renowned Swiss match pistol grip designer Cesare Morini. It breaks down easily without tools much like a Glock. The hand grip panels can be removed and replaced to fit the hand gun to the operator. It has a rear adjustable sight for windage. It has a polymer frame with a stainless steel slide with a Picatinny mount for lighting or Laser sight. Magazines are all Metal and fall freely from the magwell. All exposed metal surfaces are covered in a  black melonite finish. The gun is very accurate and scores of 100 are easy to accomplish. The best feature other than being able to fit the firearm to your hand size is the ability to decock the striker before disassembly unlike a Glock which has to be dry fired to disassemble. The gun can be left in a single action mode for true single action throughout operation or decocked for a first double action trigger stroke and then it transitions to single action. TheSW99 introduced features like a decocking button located on top of the gun's slide and a new magazine release on the trigger guard. With the S&W99 the shooter can drop the magazine with their trigger finger and with one hand, never having to change their hold on the gun.

Im getting questions both good ones and stupid ones so im going to put the answers here.

"This this a stock rifle"?  NO.  Read the Description,  It was built for maximum accuracy, 

"I don't think this is a pretty rifle, the scope is not original, and I own 15 other Mosin nagants":  Thats great buddy,  do any of them shoot groups like this?  because this rifle was not numbers matching nor was it a museum piece,  It was purchased to fill a functional role, and a shorter cheaper doner rifle filled the role, so.. This one is sold as a functional shooter.   *Note if you are a marksman or real shooter all you need to so is see the groups and a list of modifications,  trigger pull can be checked when you look at the weapon..    Please dont waist my time comparing your junk size with mine on a e-mail.. it will be deleted.

"what kind of scope and mount is that"?  The Scope mount is a re manufacture copy of the ww2 scope mount system used by finland  made by accumounts.  You can mount a PE scope on it if you want.  More Importantly you can access the Iron sights by removing the scope top from the scope base if the scope ever breaks while you are hunting / shooting.  The Scope on the rifle now is a Nikon Pro-staff variable zoom with a .308 BDC (Bulled Drop Commentator),  If you care about bolistics you will notice that the 54R round ahs a similar flight path to the American 308 out to ~500 yds.  Again you can put a PE Scope on it if you want.  but, If you want an easy to use rifle keep the NIKON on there.



From my years in the Marine Corp I can tell that this weapon was more then likely a Garrison Gun as it is cleaned with all of the original bluing in EXCELLENT SHAPE.

Barrel is Stamped   SA   1942   B   D

The reason for sale is that I do not want to scratch / beat up this beautiful weapon.  I originally built it to be a back pack / truck gun to range out to 600yds, but instead I built a small Hungarian carbine (it was smaller and already beat up) to backpack/ 4x4 with and I can range 500 yds easily with and I don't feel like damaging this beautiful weapon.

This gun is by far the best shooting Mosin Nagant many people have had their hands on. but I'm a functional gun guy and dont want to have a "safe queen".  "Just for Kicks" I put up a picture of the rifle that I built for backpacking (Its the retarded ugly looking one that that has a 2-piece stock) that i'm replacing this rifle with.  This way you can see what I had in mind,  as you can see the short, fugly,  and very functional Hungarian carbine can be used as a bat and I wont care if the stock breaks.  



Due to the cost of the Scope, Mounting system, Rifle, ammo and the time required to "free float" the barrel and other things necessary to make a rifle shoot sub MOA I'm firm on the price.   Transfer will take place at a colorado FFL dealer or mailed to an FFL dealer in your state / city.

title: For Sale:  .22 Single Action Revolver plus ammunition
location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
For sale, a Tanfoglio .22 revolver. These were made by the same people who make the EAA Witness line of pistols nowadays. I got this for my son, because I thought he would like shooting it. Well, instead, he has his sights set on a rifle so here it is. The Tanfolglio is about the same size as a Ruger or Colt .22 and though less expensive, they are good guns. They have a safety which allows them to be carried fully loaded, unlike the Colt. This was called the Swiss Safe and it works, completely blocking the hammer from making contact with the rim of the .22 round when engaged. 

It will make a good plinker or even something to use on jackrabbits and the like. The brass frame has a lot of nice patina on it and doesn't appear to have eve been polished. Bluing s a good 90-95% and the bore is perfect. It has not been used or carried much, and my son only shot about 12 rounds through it. 

Since .22 ammunition can be tough to find, I will include 100 rounds of it for you so you can go right out and shoot it. Hopefully soon the internet scalpers will stop buying all of it up at Walmart so ammunition will be easier to get soon. Rin Peterson's in ABQ and the Outdoorsman in Santa Fe are getting it regularly. Walmart too, but you just have to ask when it will come in to beat those scalpers to the punch.

I think you'll like this gun. I did and that was why we got it. The Italians make some good stuff in Gardone, Italy, (most reproduction BP guns) and this is no exception.

Contact me through Armslist with your number and I will call you to arrange a meeting. I used to put my number in these ads, but I got inundated with Nigerian princes who wanted to give me their fortunes for just a small percentage, lol.

Good shooting...

title: For Sale:  Sig 556 ER Like New Condition! 5.56 NATO piston operated semi automatic rifle
postcontent:
Insanely reliable Swiss engineering. This rifle is a pleasure to shoot, especially because of how clean it runs due to the piston operating system. Fouling in the chamber is significantly reduced and the gun can run forever.

This rifles accuracy is fantastic, due to the precision it was manufactured with. It's not a sub-MOA weapon by any means, but it's certainly more accurate than 90% of the AR's on the market. The trigger has a nice clean brake.

The 556's bolt is contained within the upper receiver for the entirety of it's operating cycle, thus the stock and "buffer tube" can be removed without any impact on the operation of the weapon.

Key Features:
-16" Bbl
-1:7 twist rate
- A2 flash hider with standard threads.
-Flat Top receiver
-M1913 rails on the bottom and sides of the handguard (unless you're running more than a PEQ, a surefire, a grip pod, and a Tac Sling Mount this is more than enough rail)

-Accepts STANAG Magazines (M16 mags)
